In a city with more than 4,000 restaurants, I've always been challenged to find a good wine bar -- and by good I mean one where the wine selection is as good as the food. In TriBeCa, though, I didn't have to wander far to find just that. Terroir TriBeCa is popular among Financial District Happy Hour goers who come in droves and while the wine menu is a bit dizzying, I'm happy to leave that to my partner and focus on the food which is simple and tasty. Wooden high top tables, bench seating and low lighting offer an ideal setting to unwind after work, catch up with friends or spend a casual date night. Read more: bit.ly/IMbNGV
